ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) can baked beans with pork
instructions: Crumble the ground beef into a large skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until beef is no longer pink.
Reduce heat to medium-low and stir in the corn, chili with beans, baked beans, tomato sauce and green chilies.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
title: Cowboy Stew I
steps: Crumble the ground beef into a large skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook and stir until beef is no longer pink. Drain off grease. Reduce heat to medium-low and stir in the corn, chili with beans, baked beans, tomato sauce and green chilies. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
